## Demo A: Learn Research-Training Proof Loop

Core message: a research learning loop should preserve learner evidence, misconceptions, review order, and re-verification without crossing into graded-work automation.

Run from any temp directory:

```powershell
$demo = Join-Path $env:TEMP ("learn-proof-demo-" + [guid]::NewGuid().ToString("N"))
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $demo | Out-Null
Push-Location $demo
node C:\dev\public\learn\src\cli.mjs tutor plan research-proof --topic "research proof packets" --objectives "source provenance,verification receipts"
node C:\dev\public\learn\src\cli.mjs tutor record research-proof --objective "source provenance" --prompt "What must a research proof packet bind?" --answer "sources to claims" --correct true
node C:\dev\public\learn\src\cli.mjs tutor record research-proof --objective "source provenance" --prompt "What detects drift?" --answer "reverification" --correct true
node C:\dev\public\learn\src\cli.mjs tutor record research-proof --objective "verification receipts" --prompt "What should a receipt carry?" --answer "hashes and verdicts" --correct false --feedback "missing action provenance"
node C:\dev\public\learn\src\cli.mjs tutor study research-proof --now 2026-07-02T00:00:00.000Z
node C:\dev\public\learn\src\cli.mjs tutor study-receipt research-proof --now 2026-07-02T00:00:00.000Z
node C:\dev\public\learn\src\cli.mjs tutor reverify research-proof
Pop-Location
```

Expected local result:

- Study plan reports one misconception and mastery `not yet`.
- Study receipt reports `verified true`.
- Reverify reports the stored receipt verifies from its evidence.

Post angle:

> Learn is not a credential bypass. It is a pressure system for evidence: practice attempts, misconceptions, study order, receipts, and re-verification.

