## Demo D: Megatool Composition

Core message: the product story is the integration, not any one tool. The same proof packet can become research evidence, a learning object, compiler/runtime evidence, and an external witness target.

Composition path:

1. Gather captures source material and emits source receipts.
2. Index selects the relevant workspace and source context with a freshness root.
3. Forum routes the work and records the handoff.
4. Crucible converts claims into `MATCH`, `DRIFT`, or `UNVERIFIABLE`.
5. Telos packages context, action, browser evidence, and loop ledgers.
6. Learn turns a proof packet into retrieval practice, misconceptions, and re-verifiable study receipts.
7. BuildLang/buildc emits source, effect, policy, backend, and corpus receipts for executable proof domains.
8. Emet independently checks byte/view consistency.

Minimal local command set:

```powershell
node demo/context-pack.mjs
node demo/action-receipt.mjs
node demo/loop-ledger.mjs
index context-envelope --root . --budget 1600 --focus telos --hops 0 --json
forum route "Continue improving the five Project Telos flagship tools as protocol agnostic enterprise AI workflow tools, and package second-wave Learn BuildLang Emet proof demos with MCP CLI compatibility, source-checkout receipts, and outreach handoff documents." --json
crucible run --thesis docs\outreach\receipts\second-wave-tooling-thesis-2026-07-02.json --measurements docs\outreach\receipts\second-wave-tooling-measurements-2026-07-02.json --out docs\outreach\receipts\second-wave-tooling-run-2026-07-02.json --report docs\outreach\receipts\second-wave-tooling-report-2026-07-02.md
```

If the Crucible report path already exists, use a fresh `--out` and `--report` path for the rerun. The CLI fails rather than silently overwriting a prior receipt.

